Superdesk API

API Endpoint

Superdesk is an open source end-to-end news creation, production, curation, distribution and publishing platform developed and maintained by Sourcefabric with the sole purpose of making the best possible software for journalism.

This is the offical documentation of Superdesk API used by Superdesk application. It features all the resources to

  • manage a newsroom (i.e. users, desks, stages etc)

  • manage stories (i.e. templates, stories, multimedia etc)

  • manage distribution (i.e. subscribers, filters, destinations etc)

Before You Begin ¶

The base URI for all requests is http://{{host}/api where host will be the host address where the server runs.

To run the server locally please check Superdesk repo for all the information

Features ¶

Below is a list of some of the main features that any Superdesk APIs can expose.

  • (Filtering)[https://docs.python-eve.org/en/stable/features.html#filtering]

  • (Sorting)[https://docs.python-eve.org/en/stable/features.html#sorting]

  • (Pagination)[https://docs.python-eve.org/en/stable/features.html#pagination]

  • (HATEOAS)[https://docs.python-eve.org/en/stable/features.html#hateoas]

PATCH and DELETE actions ¶

Patch and Delte actions will require a header If-Match with the etag value of the resource

Authentication ¶

Basic Authentication ¶

POST /auth_db
Requestsexample 1
Headers
Content-Type: application/json;charset=UTF-8
Body
{
    "username": {{uername}},
    "password": {{password}}
}
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "_status": "OK",
  "_links": {
    "self": {
      "href": "auth_db/123",
      "title": "Auth_db"
    }
  },
  "username": "user_name",
  "_etag": "35186487751b000740635868c46ec1679f35acb0",
  "_updated": "2019-06-23T04:42:52+0000",
  "token": "07b2be11-5edc-4efd-b021-h34h34434",
  "user": "5ab1a33434dfe38019f0a875a",
  "_id": "123",
  "_created": "2019-06-23T04:42:52+0000"
}

Authenticate
POST/auth_db

Uses basic authentication with username and password to authenticate the user

The rest of the endpoints requiring authorization will have to supply the following header: “Authorization”: b"basic " + b64encode(token + b"😊

Reset User Password ¶

POST /reset_user_password
Requestsexample 1example 2
Body
{
  "email": "a2@a.com"
}
Schema
{
  "email": {
    "type": "email"
  },
  "token": {
    "type": "string"
  },
  "password": {
    "type": "string"
  },
  "expire_time": {
    "type": "datetime"
  },
  "user": "{user_id}"
}
Responses201
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
    "email": "user@email.com",
    "_status": "OK",
    "_id": "5d0f6ea41d41c8f11e5a11bc",
    "expire_time": "2019-06-24T12:20:52+0000",
}
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
    "token": "emailed token"
    "password": "new password"
}
Schema
{
    "email": {"type": "email"},
    "token": {"type": "string"},
    "password": {"type": "string"},
    "expire_time": {"type": "datetime"},
    "user": "{user_id}"
}
Responses201
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
    "email": "user@email.com",
    "_status": "OK",
    "_id": "5d0f6ea41d41c8f11e5a11bc",
    "expire_time": "2019-06-24T12:20:52+0000",
}

Initiate and Complete Reset User Password
POST/reset_user_password

If email is provided starts reset password process and sends an email to users email address. If a token and password is provided, it resets the password for the user where reset password process has started.

  • email (string) - Email of user

  • token (string) - Token for reset password process

  • password (string) - New password of user

This endpoint will not be exposed if AD is enabled.

Change User Password ¶

POST /change_user_password
Requestsexample 1
Body
{
  "username": "a2@a.com",
  "old_password": "pass1",
  "new_password": "pass2"
}
Schema
{
  "username": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true
  },
  "old_password": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true
  },
  "new_password": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true
  }
}
Responses201401
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
    ["12jerppwreorie033f2f"]
}
This response has no content.

Change Reset User Password
POST/change_user_password

Changes the password if a given user to the new one

  • username (string) - Username of user

  • old_password (string) - Old password of user

  • new_password (string) - New password of user

This endpoint will not be exposed if AD is enabled.

Update password will fail if:

  • User is not found

  • Old password is not validated

If the user has needs_activation is set to true, password change will remove that flag.

Delete a User Session

Update stage
PATCH/stages/{id}

Updates the stage by given id. A stage will fail to update if:

  • If there’s no working stage remaining after the update

  • If there’s no incoming stage remaining after the update

URI Parameters
HideShow

string (required) Example: 1

stage identifier.

Body

Body

  "_message": "Cannot delete a Working Stage."
}

Delete a stage
DELETE/stages/{id}

Deletes the stage by given id. A stage will fail to delete if:

  • It is a working stage

  • Incoming stage

  • There are stories referencing to the stage

  • An ingest routing rule is referencing a stage

URI Parameters
HideShow
id
string (required) Example: 1

stage identifier.

Delete a Desk
DELETE/desks/{desk_id}

Deletes the desk by given id. A desk will fail to delete if:

  • It is assigned as default desk to a user

  • There is a routing rule referencing to the desk

  • There are items in the desk

Create A New Routing Scheme
POST/routing_schemes

Creates a new routing scheme. Creation of a routing scheme will fail if:

  • There is no rule defined in routing scheme

  • If there are multiple rules with the same name

  • If an unknown field provide in the rule definition

  • If there’s no name defined

  • If there’s no action defined in routing scheme

  • If an empty schedule is given

  • If a schedule is given and if the date and time formats are not recognized

A Routing Scheme ¶

GET /routing_schemes/routing_scheme_id
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body

  "_id": "5bc08c26bfb76600e3158e98",

      "href": "routing_schemes/5bc08c26bfb76600e3158e98"

      "title": "routing_schemes",
      "href": "routing_schemes"

  "name": "To Karel's desk",

Update A Routing Scheme
PATCH/routing_schemes/{routing_scheme_id}

Updates the routing scheme. Update of the routing scheme will fail if:

  • If all rules are removed

  • If there are multiple rules with the same name

  • If an unknown field provide in the rule definition

  • If name is removed

  • If the actions areremoved

  • If an empty schedule is given

  • If a schedule is given and if the date and time formats are not recognized

Create A New Dictionary
POST/Dictionaries

A new dictionary can be created by either providing the content field or by providing a text file in the post message. If a file is provided, it will be parsed when a new dictionary is created and the content field will be populated.

Creation of a new dictionary will fail if

  • Both content is not provided but uploaded file could not be parsed

  • If the name of the dictionary is not unique

  • If the type of the dictioary is “Abbreviations” and user field is empty

A Dictionary ¶

GET /Dictionaries/dictionary_id
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "content": {
    "MYABR": "this is my abbreviation",
    "USA": "Unated States of America",
    "WHO": "World Health Organization",
    "UN": "United Nations"
  },
  "type": "abbreviations",
  "_id": "5ccb2223739a48801f753d9e",
  "_created": "2019-05-02T17:00:19+0000",
  "name": "5ab27997cdfe38023cd29e97:en",
  "language_id": "en",
  "_etag": "815ba73d64e5c590b28a074874ef7793ae3aca6a",
  "user": "5ab27997cdfe38023cd29e97",
  "_updated": "2019-05-02T17:00:19+0000",
  "_file_id": null,

Update A Dictionary
PATCH/Dictionaries/{dictionary_id}

A dictionary can be updated by either providing the content field or by providing a text file in the post message. If a file is provided, it will be parsed when the dictionary is updated. The existing content will be merged with the new one.

Update of a new dictionary will fail if

  • Both content is not provided but uploaded file could not be parsed

  • If the name of the dictionary is not unique

  • If dictionary type is different

URI Parameters
HideShow
dictionary_id
string (required) 

Dictionary id

Requestsexample 1

Body

Create A New Concept Item
POST/Concept Items

Creation of concept items will fail if:

  • ‘languages’ vocabulary is not set in the system

  • Labels are not unique

  • Wrong cpnat_type is provided

Create A New Content Template
POST/content_templates

Creating a new Content Templates will fail if:

  • If the following fields are given for a Kill template: – “schedule”, “dateline”, “template_desks”, “schedule_desk”,“schedule_stage”

  • If kill template is assigned to a desk

  • If kill template is not public

  • If templare is assigned to multiple desks for a “Create” type template

Delete A Content Type

vocabulary id

Internal Destinations ¶

Internal Destinations Collection ¶

When an item is published, it will be copied and send to a selected desk defined in internal destinations. Item is first checked against content filters and the action is performed only with item that matches the filter criteria. Users can select the desk, its stage and a macro to be run on the item (optional). The macro usually modifies the item (e.g. changes its metadata) but it can be also used to publish the modified item

GET /internal_destinations
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "_items": [
    {
      "_id": "5c18b4c0bfb76600e48c7f6c",
      "name": "test",
      "_etag": "32c54c9c60e71f279553ab7e0569f9d85a21aab9",
      "is_active": false,
      "_updated": "2018-12-18T08:55:33+0000",
      "stage": "5ba0eab7bfb76600df7fd6ab",
      "_links": {
        "self": {
          "title": "Internal_destination",
          "href": "internal_destinations/5c18b4c0bfb76600e48c7f6c"
        }
      },
      "filter": "5b7e6eecbfb76600e0a4ea31",
      "_created": "2018-12-18T08:50:08+0000",
      "desk": "5ba0eab7bfb76600df7fd6ad"
    }

Create A New Item
POST/archive

When a new item is posted some of the fields in the schema is autogenerated on the server

  • A new guid and _id fields are assigned to a new value (their values will be the same)

  • A unique_id is assigned to story that is unique in archive collection

  • A family_id is copied from guid. For cloned stories family_id is preserved across clones.

  • An event_id is assigned

  • state is set to Draft

  • source is assigned the value of the ingest provide if the item is fetched. Otherwise if there is a default source for the desk the item is created then that source is assigned. Otherwise the source in the global settings will be assigned.

  • If the item has a profile field or if there"s a global profile is assigned, then story will copy the metadata from all the fields defined in the content type of the profile.

  • If there are default values assigned for fields priority, genre, urgency then they will be populated

  • If there are default preferences defined for the user for fields dateline, byline, place then they will be populated

  • signoff field is updated:

    1. sign_off = sign_off of original + sign_off of the user performing operation.
    2. If the last modified user and the user performing operation are same then sign_off shouldn"t change
    3. If sign_off is received on updates, this value will be preserved
    4. If a users sign_off is already in the list then it will be removed and appended to the end

  • word_count will be calculated

  • expiry is set according to expiry values on stage, or desk, or global settings

  • If there are metada defined in the desk then desk metada will be reflected on the item

Creation of a new item will fail if:

  • Stage is a readonly stage

  • If there"s a schedule provided but the date is in the past or date is not recognized

Media Sources

  • If there"s a url in the media field of the item then the media will be fetched as a file

  • If there"s a file reference to the item in media field, that file will be user_marked

  • Renditions will be generated for picture files. Renditions are defined in vocabularies.

An Item ¶

This endpoint will return the details of an item in archive collection. It will fail to return if:

  • Item is in an invisible stage
GET /archive/item_id

Update A Story
PATCH/archive/{item_id}

When an archive item is updated the following actions take place in the system:

  • Update of an archive item saves the current version of the item and saves the changes as a new version.

  • If there is a picture in the updates then renditions will be created

  • versioncreated field is assigned the current date value

  • version_creator field is assigned the user id

  • word_count field is updated

Update of an archive item will fail if:

  • item is locked by another user

  • state of the article is Killed or Recalled

  • user is trying to update the package with Public Service Announcements

  • user is authorized to update unique name of the article

  • user is trying to update the genre of a broadcast article

  • article being scheduled and is in a package

  • article being scheduled and schedule timestamp is invalid

  • article has valid crops if the article type is a picture

  • article is a valid package if the article type is a package

  • article has a valid Embargo

  • item is on readonly stage.

URI Parameters
HideShow
item_id
string (required) 

item id

Archive Copy Resource ¶

This endpoint will copy a draft item in users private workspace.Copy function fail is the item is on a desk.

  • Item is in an invisible stage

Archive Duplicate Resource ¶

This endpoint will duplicate an item and move it to given desk and stage. Duplication will fail if there is no desk and stage provided. sign_off field of the duplicated item will be updated by duplicator id. Duplicated item will have a new event_id

  • Item is in an invisible stage
POST /archive/item_id/duplicate
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{}

    "type": "string",
    "required": true

    "type": "string",
    "required": false
  }

Archive Move Resource ¶

This endpoint will move an item to a given desk and stage. Duplication will fail if:

  • Item is locked by another user

  • If the stage is the same as current stage

  • If the item is a published item

last_production_desk and last_authoring_desk fields of the moved item will be updated.

When item moves from one stage to another there are three macros can runs against the item if they defined for the original and destination stages:

  • Outgoing Macro of original stage

  • Incoming Macro of destination stage

  • OnStage Macro of destination stage

POST /archive/item_id/move
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "task": {
    "desk": "d4354sa8d7sdsaod",
    "stage": "asd3o32423asdu00a99as9"
  }
}
Schema
{
    "task": {
        "type": "dict",
        "required": true,
        "schema": {
            "desk": {"type": "string", "required": true},
            "stage": {"type": "string", "required": true}
        }
    },
    "allPackageItems": {"type": "boolean", "required": false, "nullable": true},
}

Move An Item

Archive Lock Resource ¶

Locks the story for a given user. This will prevent other users editing or moving the item. Once the item is locked, it will we added to users “workspace” collection. Lock action will fail if the item is already locked by another user or by same user in another session.

Archive Resend Resource ¶

Resends a published item to distribution channels. Resend will fail if

  • If the item is not a published, corrected of killed ite

  • If there is a newer version of the item

  • It the item is rewritten (another rewrite story exists)

  • If it is not a text item

  • If the item has not been sent to at least one subscriber

POST /archive/item_id/resend
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "subscribers": [
    "54fe438b10245412e5608d41"
  ],
  "version": 2
}
Schema
{
  "subscribers": {
    "type": "list"
  },
  "version": {
    "type": "integer"
  }

Archive Rewrite Resource ¶

Replaces an item by creating a new item. A new item can be created automatically by providing the desk_id in the payload. An existing item can be linked as the rewrite of an item by providing its id in update field in the payload

Rewrite will fail if:

  • the original item is rewritten before

  • original item has an embargo defined

  • original item is a rewrite and is not published yet

  • original item does not have an event_id

  • content profile of the original item is not the same as content profile of the rewrite

  • rewrite is not a text or broadcast item

POST /archive/item_id/rewrite
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "desk_id": "54fe438b10245412e5608d41"
}
Schema
{
  "desk_id": {
    "type": "string",
    "nullable": true
  },
  "update": {
    "type": "dict",
    "nullable": true
  }
}

Spike ¶

Spikes an item. Spiked item has the references to the other items (such as rewrites) removed. A spiked item can have a new expiry value depending on the global setting SPIKE_EXPIRY_MINUTES defined in the system

Unspike ¶

Unspikes an item. When an item is unspiked it restores to the previous desk and stage. It won"t recover lost links to other items. It will have the expiry of the desk/stage it is on.

Translate ¶

Translates a given story from the language defined in the item to a language given by using the translation macro defined in the system. Translation will create a new item with the translated content and will return the new id. If the item is a package then the contents of the package will be translated and the new items will be copied into the same package.

Tranlation will fail if:

  • Item with id not found
POST /archive/translate/item_id
Requestsexample 1
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "guid": "123",
  "language": "de"
}
Schema
{
    "guid": {

        "type": "string",
        "required": true

        "type": "string",

        "nullable": true
    },
}

Autosave an Archive Item
POST/archive_autosave

Autosave is used to save the ongoing edits on an archive item. The snapshot of the item can be saved by posting to this endpoint. Autosave will fail if there is not story found with the given id.

An autosaved item ¶

Archive Publishing ¶

Publish ¶

Publishing an item updates the state to published. Item is then moved to published repo from archive when item expires. Item will also be copied to legal_archive collection with the complete versions when it is published. Published item becomes a read-only item but it is possible to create post publish actions like corrections and rewrites. Those actions usually create a new item and keeps the original item intact.

When an item is published, system will generate entries in publish_queue which then will be processed to send the item to matching subscribers. All the new entries in publish_queue will also be coped to legal_publish_queue collection as well.

When an item is published, it will need to compy with publish validation rules. They are defined in system settings, validations.

If the item has publish_schedule field defined, then when it is published, it will have the state scheduled but it won’t be sent to matching subscribers until the schedule date and time.

Publish of an item will fail if:

  • item is marked as not_for_publication

  • item state is in draft

PATCH /archive/publish/item_id
Requestsexample 1
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: {_etag}
Body
{
  "state": "published"
}
Responses200403
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Headers
Content-Type: application/json

Publish An Item
PATCH/archive/publish/{item_id}

Publishes an item.

URI Parameters
HideShow
item_id
string (required) 

item id

Correct ¶

Published item can be locked and corrected. When an item published as correction, it will go through the same steps in publish action. Corrections will be sent to the same list of subscribers where the original item is published to. Corrections cannot be scheduled.

PATCH /archive/correct/item_id
Requestsexample 1
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: {_etag}
Body
{
  "state": "corrected"
}
Responses200403
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Headers
Content-Type: application/json

Correct An Item
PATCH/archive/correct/{item_id}

Corrects an item.

URI Parameters
HideShow
item_id
string (required) 

item id

Kill ¶

Published or corrected items can be killed. When an item is killed, the kill template in the system gets applied to the item to update the contents to fit the kill message. When an item killed, it will go through the same steps in publish action.Killed item will be sent to same set of subscribers. If a broadcast item is killed, it will kill the master item as well. An item within a packed can be killed once it is removed from the package.

PATCH /archive/kill/item_id
Requestsexample 1
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: {_etag}
Body
{
  "state": "killed"
}
Responses200403
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Headers
Content-Type: application/json

Mark An Item
POST/marked_for_highlights

Generate Highlights ¶

Creates a new itemt using the highlight package. A highlight package is to container for all items marked for highlights. A highligh package will have type field as composite and highight_id field populated with id of the highlight definition. The new item will use the template defined in the highlight to produce the text item.

If preview option is provided in the payload then new item will be returned but not saved in the system as a new item.

Highlight generation will fail if:

  • Any of the items marked as highlight is either locked or in published states
POST /generate_highlights
Requestsexample 1
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "package": "urn:newsml:localhost:5000:2017-10-01T12:00:45.929411:4d212c20-febf-41e7-9097-6aaa42b2cd31"
}
Schema
{
    "package": {
        "type": "string",
        "required": true,
    },
    "preview": {
        "type": "boolean",
        "default": false,
    },
    "export": {
        "type": "boolean",
        "default": false,
    }
}
Responses201403
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Headers
Content-Type: application/json

Generate a highlights item
POST/generate_highlights

Archived ¶

Archived Collection ¶

Archived collection contains the items that has been published in the system. Every item that has been published, corrected, killed, rewritten will be copied to this collection once they expire in archive collection. Field last_published_version is set to true for last published version of the item in the published collection and for the older version is set to false. This field is used to display the last version of the digital copy in the published view.

Delete A Archived Item
DELETE/archived/{item_id}

Deletes the archived item by given id. Delete action is used for kill action. Delete will fail if:

  • item exists in published collection as well

  • item exists in a package

Perform Media Editing
POST/media_editor

Performs a media edit action on a whole item or an item_id from archive collection. It uses renditions of the item to locate the media. It is also possible to upload edit object with edition instructions.

Edition instructions keys are operations names, and values are operations parameters.

So far, the following operations are available:

  • rotate (value are counter clockwise degrees)

  • flip (value can be “vertical”, “horizontal” or “both”)

  • brightness (value is a float)

  • contrast (value is a float)

  • saturation (value is a float)

  • grayscale (value not used)

Perform Renditions
POST/picture_renditions

Creates the renditions of a given media item. It uses superdesk defual rendition definitions defined in config. if no_custom_crops false then it will also use the rendition specs defined in vocabularies

Published Items ¶

Published Items Collection ¶

Published Items collection contains all the published items in the system. When an item is published, corrected, killed or rewritten there will be a new item in published collection. Every publish action will create new entry so even if the same item is publihed then corrected, all published versions will be preserved as separate entries in this collection.

List All Published Items
GET/published

A Published Item ¶

last_published_version field is set to true for last published version of the item in the published collection and for the older version is set to false. This field is used to display the last version of the copy in the published view.

moved_to_legal field tells if item is moved to legal. True if moved else false.

Create A New Saved Search
POST/saved_searches

When a saved search is created user field will be populated automatically by the request user. If field is_global has value true then saved search will be accessable by all users. Saving a new search will fail if:

  • There are subscribers in the saved search

  • There is no filter defined

  • The given filter fails to run

  • There is no name given for the search

A Saved Search ¶

Create A New Contact
POST/contacts?

Create a new contact. Descriptions of some of the fields are:

  • public: flag to indicate that the contact item should not be publicly visible, for example if the item relates to a contact that can not be distributed due to privacy concerns

  • is_active: lag to mark the contact item active/inactive for example if the item relates to a contact that is no longer valid

  • usage: usage may provide information as to the usage of the number e.g. Business hours only

  • public: If public is true then the number can be made public, if false it is only visible in the system

Search ¶

Search Collection ¶

Basic search returns the documents where the search keyword(s) are matched in any of the fields available in ElasticSearch. Query is passed in source field and the details of query language in use is here

GET /search?repo=List of collection names to perform the search. ["ingest", "archive", "archived", "published"]?source=elasctic query dsl query to perform?aggs=0 or 1. If 1 it will return an **aggeraagations** dictionary in the results?es_highlight=string value to highlight the results for that term?projections=List of field names to return in the results
Requestsexample 1
Body
{

        aggregations=1&

        source={"query":{"filtered":{"filter":{"and":[{"not":{"term":{"state":"spiked"}}},{"or":[{"and":[{"term":{"state":"draft"}},{"term":{"original_creator":"5ab1aabdcdfe38019f0a875a"}}]},{"not":{"terms":{"state":["draft"]}}}]},{"not":{"term":{"package_type":"takes"}}}]},"query":{"query_string":{"query":"test","lenient":false,"default_operator":"AND"}}}},"sort":[{"versioncreated":"desc"}],"post_filter":{"and":[{"terms":{"task.desk":["5ab1b3ebcdfe38023cd29e55"]}}]},"size":50,"from":0}

Perform A Search
GET/search{?repo}{?source}{?aggs}{?es_highlight}{?projections}

URI Parameters
HideShow
repo
string (required) Example: List of collection names to perform the search. ["ingest", "archive", "archived", "published"]
aggs
string (required) Example: 0 or 1. If 1 it will return an **aggeraagations** dictionary in the results
es_highlight
string (required) Example: string value to highlight the results for that term
projections
string (required) Example: List of field names to return in the results
source
string (required) Example: elasctic query dsl query to perform

Create a new Ingest Provider
POST/ingest_providers

You can create an ingest provider by providing a JSON object containing a question and a collection of answers in the form of choices.

  • notifications (object) - Events that system will send notifications

  • critical_errors (object) - List of errors will cause to close the provider

  • feeding_service (string) - Type of the feeding feeding_service

  • config (object) - Connection settings to ingest source

  • update_schedule (object) - Interval between pull events

  • content_expiry (number) - ttl for ingested items in minutes

  • content_types (array[string]) - List of content types of items to ingest from provider

  • name (string) - provider name

  • source (string) - name of the source

  • is_closed (boolean) -

Delete An Ingest Item
DELETE/ingest/{ingest_id}

Deletes the ingest item by given id. It also deletes all the media items referenced by the ingest item.

URI Parameters
HideShow
ingest_id
string (required) 

ingest id

Fetch ¶

Fetches an ingest item from ingest collection into archive collection. The version in ingest collection stays in ingest and can be fecthed may times. Fetched item is moved to the desk or stage provided. Also if a macro given, that macro will be performed against the item. Fetch action will fetch all the related items suc as package items or media items as well.

POST /ingest/ingest_id/fetch
Responses201400
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Headers
Content-Type: application/json

Create A New Filter Condition
POST/filter_conditions

A new filter condition creation fails if:

  • The provided field or operator is not recognized

  • If the same filter condition with the same name already exists

  • If the same filter condition with the same field, operator and value already exists

A Filter Condition ¶

GET /filter_conditions/filter_condition_id
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
    "value": "text,preformatted,audio,video,picture,graphic,composite,planning,event",
    "operator": "in",
    "_id": "5bd85471eff91400f7a545f4",
    "name": "Unfiltered",
    "field": "type",
}

List All Filter Conditions Parameters
GET/filter_conditions/parameters

Returns the list of all the fields in the system that can be used in creating a filter condition. Every field includes the list of operators available for that field.

Create A New Content Filter
POST/content_filters

Content filters contains one or many expressions. Expressions can have list of filter condition ids in the field fc or other content filters in the field pf. Creation of the content filter fails if:

  • References filter condition or content filter does not exist

  • There is a circular reference between content filters

A Content Filter ¶

GET /content_filters/content_filter_id
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
    "is_archived_filter": false,
    "is_global": false,
    "_id": "5bd85af1eff91400ef4022a7",
    "name": "all using unfiltered",
    "api_block": false,
    "content_filter": [
        {
            "expression": {
                "fc": [
                    "5bd85471eff91400f7a545f4"
                ]
            }
        }
    ],
}

Search Content API Items
GET/search_capi?{aggregations}&{default_operator}&{max_results}&{q}&{filter}&{page}&{sort}

URI Parameters
HideShow
aggregations
number (optional) Example: 0, 1

If the aggregations should be included in the results.

default_operator
string (optional) Example: AND

Default logical operator for the queries and filters .

max_results
string (optional) Example: 25

Maximum number of results to be returned .

q
string (optional) Example: ``

Query string (ex: “slugline:(reuters)”)

filter
string (optional) Example: ``

Filter statement (ex: “[{“or”:[{“terms”:{“subject.code”:[“02001001”]}},{“terms”:{“subject.parent”:[“02001001”]}}]}]”)

page
number (optional) Example: 1

Page number

sort
string (optional) Example: ``

Sort statement (ex: “[(“versioncreated”, -1)]”)

Create A New Event
POST/events

When an event is recreated, depending on the recurring_rule there will be event records generated to reflect recurrent events.

If field duplicate_from is set when posting, then newly generated event will be the duplicate of the event provided in that field.

Creation of a new event will fail if:

  • unique_name field is not unique

Event Lock Resource ¶

Locks the event for a given user. This will prevent other users editing or moving the item. Lock will fail if:

  • there is a locked associated planning item within the event and that is locked to another user

  • the event is a recurring event and one of the instances is locked to another user

POST /events/event_id/lock
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "lock_action": "edit"
}
Schema
{
  "lock_action": {
    "type": "string"
  }
}

Event Unlock Resource ¶

Unlocks the event for a given user. This will let other users editing or moving the item. Unlocking an event from a recurring series unlocks the actual locked event.

POST /events/event_id/unlock

Content-Type: application/json

Spike An Event
PATCH/events/spike/{event_id}

Spikes an event. Based on the update_method provided, spikes “future”, “all” or “single” event in the series. Historic events, i.e. events that have already occurred, will not be spiked. Spike will fail if:

  • another Event or Planning item is currently locked

  • event is a public event

  • event has a planning item

  • event is rescheduled

  • event is already spiked

URI Parameters
HideShow
event_id
string (required) 

event id

Reschedules An Event
PATCH/events/reschedule/{event_id}

Rescheduling changes the state of the event and all the associated planning items to rescheduled. reason field could be used to give a description of the rescheduling action. Reschedule action also could update the recurrent events schedule and number of them in the system. It is possible to reschedule a postponed event. If the rescheduled event is published, then reschedule will trigger an update of the publish

URI Parameters
HideShow
event_id
string (required) 

event id

Update Time
PATCH/event/update_time/{event_id}

Event must be locked to update the time. Time update action also could update the recurrent events schedule. This is controlled by update_method field provided which could have “all”, “single”, “future” as values. It is possible to update the time of a postponed event. If the event is published, then resupdte time chedule will trigger an update of the publish

URI Parameters
HideShow
event_id
string (required) 

event id

Update Repititions of An Event ¶

Updates the number of instances of the recurring event in the system. This could be done by:

  • endRepeatMode as count so system will create the number of repititions

  • endRepeatMode as until so system will calculate the number of repititions

System can increase or decrease the number of instance by the difference in old and new dates.

Update eill fail if the target event is not an recurring event.

PATCH /events/update_repititions/event_id
Requestsexample 1
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: {_etag}
Body
{
  "dates": {
    "start": "2029-11-22T12:00:00.000Z",
    "end": "2029-11-22T14:00:00.000Z",
    "tz": "Australia/Sydney",
    "recurring_rule": {
      "frequency": "DAILY",
      "interval": 1,
      "count": 4,
      "endRepeatMode": "count"
    }
  }
}
Responses200403
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Headers

Responses200403
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Headers
Content-Type: application/json

Cancel An Event
PATCH/events/cancel/{event_id}

Cancel changes the state of the event and all the associated planning items to cancelled. reason field could be used to give a description of the cancel action. Cancel action updates the recurrent instances of the event. Cancel action also updates ednotes fields in the event and the planning item automatically to add the reason of the cancellation.

Cancel action will fail if the event is not locked to the user sending the action. If a published event cancelled, event will be published again with cancel information automatically. Only events in states “draft”, “scheduled”, “ingested”, “killed” and “postponed” can be cancelled

URI Parameters
HideShow
event_id
string (required) 

event id

Postpone An Event ¶

Postpones an event by given event id.

PATCH /events/postpone/event_id

Postpone An Event
PATCH/events/postpone/{event_id}

Postpone changes the state of the event and all the associated planning items to postponed. reason field could be used to give a description of the postpone action. Postpone action updates the recurrent instances of the event. Postpone action also updates ednotes fields in the event and the planning item automatically to add the reason of the postpone.

Postpone action will fail if the event is not locked to the user sending the action. If a published event postponed, event will be published again with postpone information automatically. Only events in states “draft”, “scheduled”, “ingested”, “killed” and “postponed” can be postponed

URI Parameters
HideShow
event_id
string (required) 

event id

Post
POST/events/post

Publishes the event to subscribers. First the event will be validated against the schema. Any error that is returned from validation will be returned as a 400 error. update_method can be used to publish all, future or a single event.

Event Planning Search ¶

Event Planning Search Collection ¶

Basic search returns event and planning documents where the search keyword(s) are matched in any of the fields available in ElasticSearch. Query is passed in source field and the details of query language in use is here

GET /event_planning_search?date_filter=Predefined list of dates "Today", "Tomorrow", "This Week" and "Next Week"?full_text=Text to search across all fields?max_results=Number of results to be returned?page=page number to be returned?posted=Flag to return only posted items?spike_state=Flag to include or exclude spiked items. "draft" for excluding spiked items, "spiked", "both"?calendars=List of calendars?agendas=List of agendas?start_date=Start date?anpa_category=Anpa category to search?state=State of the item?subject=Subject of the item
Requestsexample 1
Body
{
    /api/events_planning_search?
        anpa_category=["politics"]&
        date_filter=tomorrow&
        full_text=opera&
        max_results=50&
        page=1&
        posted=false&
        spike_state=both&
        state=["scheduled"]&
        subject=["03000000"]&
        tz_offset=+10:00
}

Perform A Search
GET/event_planning_search{?date_filter}{?full_text}{?max_results}{?page}{?posted}{?spike_state}{?calendars}{?agendas}{?start_date}{?anpa_category}{?state}{?subject}

URI Parameters
HideShow
date_filter
string (required) Example: Predefined list of dates "Today", "Tomorrow", "This Week" and "Next Week"
full_text
string (required) Example: Text to search across all fields
max_results
string (required) Example: Number of results to be returned
page
string (required) Example: page number to be returned
posted
0 or 1 (required) Example: Flag to return only posted items
spike_state
string (required) Example: Flag to include or exclude spiked items. "draft" for excluding spiked items, "spiked", "both"
start_date
string (required) Example: Start date
anpa_category
ex: ["politics"] (required) Example: Anpa category to search
state
ex: ["scheduled"] (required) Example: State of the item
subject
ex: ["03000000"] (required) Example: Subject of the item
calendars
ex: ["sports"] (required) Example: List of calendars
agendas
ex: ["sports"] (required) Example: List of agendas

Create A New Event Planning Filter
POST/events_planning_filters

Creation of the event planning filter fail is:

  • there is no agenda or calendar provided

  • name is not unique

Create A New Planning Item
POST/planning

Creates a new planning item. During the creation system will check if there’a a planning_type record. If headline is enabled in planning_type then it will use the name of the event in the headline field.

A Planning Item ¶

Update A Planning Item
PATCH/planning/{planning_id}

  • Canceling a coverage will cancel the assignment item.

  • Updating internal_notes field will raise an interna event

  • Updating scheduled times for coverages will raise an internal event

  • Updates to planning items will be recorded in planning history entity

Planning item update will fail if:

  • A coverage is removed but there’s an assignment for the coverage

  • Planning item does not exist

  • An assignment is removed but there’s a non draft state coverage for the assignment

  • A coverage is updated but the related assignment does not exist

URI Parameters
HideShow
planning_id
string (required) 

planning id

Planning Item Duplicate Resource ¶

Duplicates the given planning item. Duplicating a Planning item will link to the same Planning Item. But if the planning item is expired, the link to event will be removed.

If the duplicated planning item has been published, duplicate won’t get auto published. Coverages in the duplicate will revert to draft state.

POST /planning/planning_id/duplicate
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{}
Schema
{}

Duplicate A Planning Item
POST/planning/{planning_id}/duplicate

URI Parameters
HideShow
planning_id
string (required) 

planning item id

Planning Item Lock Resource ¶

Locks the planning item for a given user. This will prevent other users editing or moving the item. Lock will fail if:

  • the planning item is locked to another user

  • the planning item is recurring and another instance of recurrances is locked to another user

POST /planning/planning_id/lock
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "lock_action": "edit"
}
Schema
{
  "lock_action": {
    "type": "string"
  }
}

Lock An Planning Item

URI Parameters
HideShow
planning_id
string (required) 

planning item id

Planning Item Unlock Resource ¶

Unlocks the planning item for a given user. This will let other users editing or moving the item. Unlock will fail if:

  • Lock is not created by the same user

  • planning item does not exist

  • there’s no lock on item

POST /planning/planning_id/unlock
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json

Cancel An Planning Item
PATCH/planning/cancel/{planning_id}

Cancel changes the state of the planning item cancelled. reason field could be used to give a description of the cancel action. Cancel action updates the recurrent instances of the planning item. Cancel action also updates ednotes fields in the planning item and the planning item automatically to add the reason of the cancellation.

Cancel action will fail if the planning item is not locked to the user sending the action. If a published planning item cancelled, planning item will be published again with cancel information automatically.

If cancel_all_coverage is provided with value true in the payload then all coverages in the planning will be cancelled. When the coverage is cancelled, it’s links to archive items wil be removed automatically.

If event_cancellation is provided with value true in the payload then the event will be cancelled.

URI Parameters
HideShow
planning_id
string (required) 

planning id

Postpone A Planning Item
PATCH/planning/postpone/{planning_id}

Postpone changes the state of the planning item to postponed. reason field could be used to give a description of the postpone action. Postpone action postpones the coverages. Postpone action also updates ednotes fields in the planning item automatically to add the reason of the postpone.

Postpone action will raise an event for the assigments

URI Parameters
HideShow
planning_id
string (required) 

planning id

Planning Article Export ¶

Planning Article Export Collection ¶

Exports the planning item as a new archive item fornatted with the given article template. Archive item then is used to render the output in string using the template provided in the template field. Templates are retrieved from planning_export_templates endpoint.

Article export will fail if:

  • Template does not exist

  • Article template does not exist

  • Planning item does not exist

POST /planning_article_export
Requestsexample 1

  ],
  "desk": "5ab27997cdfe38023cd29e97"

Validate A Planning Item
POST/planning_validator

Validates a planning item. This endpoint is called internally when a planning item is posted.

Validation will fail if:

  • there is no validator defined for the planning item type

  • the planning item is not valid

Planning Types ¶

Planning Types Collection ¶

Returns what fields should be shown in the edit forms in planning, in the edit dictionary. Also provides a schema to allow the client to validate the values entered in the forms. Entries can be overridden by providing alternates in the planning_types mongo collection.

Create A New Featured Planning
POST/planning_featured

Creates a new featured planning entry for the day. Planning items that are provided in the list field should all have the field featured to be true.

When a new featured planning is created, the planning items within the list will be expected to be posted. System will post the featured planning entry itself with the list of alredy posted planning items if posted field is set to true.

Creating a new featured planning entry will fail if:

  • At least one of the provided planning items is not posted before

  • At least one of the provided planning items has featured flag as false or empty

  • There"s an existing featured planning entry for the day

Assignments ¶

The life cycle of an Assignment

  • A Coverage can be assigned to a desk or to a desk and user. From within planning, for example, an editor may decide to assign a coverage to a desk or bureau and allow them to decide which staffer does the work, or the editor may decide to assign directly to a user.

  • If a coverage is assigned to a desk, a user needs to be a member of that desk in order to see it in their list of assignments, and the item will be created on that desk.

  • The work for a coverage assignment should always be created on a desk. It should not be possible to fulfill a coverage within a personal workspace

  • The default (initial) state of an assignment is ‘assigned’ This means that the Coverage is assigned to workflow but work has not started.

  • Once an associated (linked) content item is created, the assignment status is changed to “in progress”.

  • When an assignment is configured with a ‘coverage provider’ the ‘start working’ action to create a new content item will not be available.

  • When an ‘in progress’ text assignment is completed by a user on an authoring desk they will then send the item to a production desk. In this workflow case, the assignment status will change to ‘submitted’ and there will also be a change of desk assignment so that the story assignment now appears in the assignment list for the production desk (with no [assigned_user]). When a user on the production desk then edits the submitted story, the assignment status will again change to ‘in progress’ and the [assigned_user] value will reflect the current lock user.

  • Once/When an item linked to an Assignment is published, the assignment status is changed to “completed”.

  • A User can also manually mark an assignment as complete.

  • Once an assignment has been completed, no further actions are available against it. For example, a User cannot “re-assign” an assignment if it has already been completed.

  • If a user who has accepted an assignment partially completes it before reassigning it back to the desk (or to another user), any content that may have already been created from the Assignment is left untouched. This might for example occur if a user who is working on an assignment needs to switch to another, leaving their original assignment to be picked up by someone else.

  • A coverage (and its related Assignment) can be cancelled. If there has been any content already generated for a cancelled coverage the content will be left ‘as is’ in the system, but with all references to planning removed

Assignments Collection ¶

GET /assignments

Create A New Assignment
POST/assignments

An assigment can have the following states:

  • draft: Assignments are created in draft when coverage is in draft status

  • assigned - The work of fulfilling the coverage has been assigned to a Desk or to a Desk & User in combination

  • in progress - Work has been started on the coverage assignment and a content item has been linked

  • completed - Work has been completed (published in the case of a text item)

  • submitted - Work has been sent from one desk to another desk.

  • cancelled - The related Coverage has been cancelled.

New assignment creation will fail if:

  • there"s no desk provided

  • the desk is different than the desk of the assignment

  • planning item does not exist

  • coverage does not exist

Delete A Assignment
DELETE/assignments/{assignment_id}

Delete of an assignment will fail if:

  • lock could not be obtained for the assignment

  • lock is not obtained on the associated Planning item or Event

  • if the assignment is already completed

URI Parameters
HideShow
assignment_id
string (required) 

assignment id

Assignment Lock Resource ¶

Locks the assignment for a given user. This will prevent other users editing or moving the item. Lock will fail if:

  • there is a lock on the assignment by another user

  • the assignment is not in “assigned”, “completed”, “submitted” or “in_progress” states

  • associated content item is locked by another user

POST /assignments/assignment_id/lock
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "lock_action": "edit"
}
Schema
{
  "lock_action": {
    "type": "string"
  }
}

Assignment Unlock Resource ¶

Unlocks the assignment for a given user. This will let other users editing or moving the item.

  • Unlocking archive item unlocks assignment

  • Unlocking assignment has no effect is linked content is still locked

Assignments Complete Resource ¶

Creates content for a given assignment. Updates the state of the assignment to in_progress It aso updates the following fields of the assignment:

  • assigned_to.desk

  • assigned_to.user

  • assigned_to.assignor_user

  • assigned_to.assignt_dateuser

Create Content for An Assignment
POST/assignments/complete

Assignments Link Resource ¶

A user would need to link Superdesk Text Items to Planning Items in the following cases:

  • An assignment has been created for a reporter and the reporter submits the content via email or google forms (not using Superdesk).

  • An assignment has not been created for a reporter and the reporter submits content via email or google forms (not using Superdesk) that needs to be linked back to planning

  • An assignment has been created for a Desk/User and the content is covered by agency content (Reuters, PA, etc)

  • An assignment has not been created for a Desk/User and the content is covered by agency copy.

  • There is a need to link an unlinked Superdesk story to a Coverage assignment

Link action will fail if:

  • assignment does not exist

  • content item does not exist

  • content is already linked to an assignment

  • content not in workflow

  • a content already exists for the assignment

POST /assignments/link
Responses200
Headers
Content-Type: application/json
Body
{
  "assignment_id": "123123ef4523ce2",
  "item_id": "123123ef4523ce2",

  },

    "required": true

    "type": "boolean",
    "required": true
  }

Link An Assignment
POST/assignments/link

Assignments Revert Resource ¶

Reverts the status of the assignment back to the value in revert_status field. Non-Text Assignments should be in completed status for revert action.

Revert action will fail if:

  • the assignment is a text assignment

  • assignment is not completed
